To investigate morphological character of curcumin loaded CS/CQDs/ Fe2O3 nano particles, FE-SEM analysis has been conducted. Results of this analysis has been demonstrated in fig below (Fig. 4
                        ). This result exhibits distinct spherical shapes with smooth surfaces. As reported in previous articles, in drug delivery applications, spherical nanoparticles have the highest efficiency [69]. Smooth surface assures homogenous blending along with compatibility between selected nanoparticles. W/O/W double emulsion method is evident in this figure, which is strongly effective in controlling the release of the hydrophobic drug, curcumin, from the internal aqueous phase since oil layer acts as membrane, and thus it can contribute in prolonging the release period. Chitosan adhesive trait forms a matrix structure, which is evident in the picture below. Histogram graph (Fig. 5
                        ) is in consistent agreement with DLS results.
